    <string name="main_app_tagline">App for downloading video/audio from YouTube, playback, sharing files, and local streaming (Chromecast).</string>
    <string name="cd_sites_note">Note: links, sharing, supported sites</string>

    <string name="main_sites_note_title">Note — links &amp; sites</string>
    <string name="main_sites_note_intro">You can use links from other sites (not only YouTube) in two ways:\n\n• Paste the address into the “URL or search” field below, then tap “Search”.\n\n• From a browser or the YouTube app (or another app), use “Share” and pick DLPulse — this app opens and you can download video or audio (pick quality) or only analyze the link.\n\nTechnically, downloads use yt-dlp (see below).</string>

    <string name="main_sites_info_body"><![CDATA[DLPulse Android project page (source & official releases):
https://github.com/calvarr/DLPulse-android

Note: not only YouTube — this app uses yt-dlp and can download from many other sites when an extractor exists.

Official list of sites (long, updated often):
https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp/blob/master/supportedsites.md

Extractor documentation:
https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp/wiki/Extractors

On a terminal (Linux / macOS / Windows) you can list all extractors:
yt-dlp --list-extractors

Filter output (example: lines containing “youtube”):
yt-dlp --list-extractors | grep -i youtube]]></string>

